msDesc.head: St Birgitta, Revelations; Simon of Cascia; Bernhardinus of Siena; Richard Rolle of Hampole, De emendatione peccatorum; Theological texts; Ars Moriendi QS

p.note: Upper left corner, in pencil in a modern hand: illegible notes.

binding.p: Rebound with new flyleaves in 1979. Loose cover with broad support bands. Four raised bands on spine.

16th-century covers, belonging to a work not related to the contents of the manuscript. Traces of a book plate on . Top of , in brown ink: illegible title. Below in brown ink: 390. Bottom of , stamped in gold: A 68. These covers are kept in a separate box.

origin.p: Germany ca 1475 based on the watermarks.

acquisition.p: Purchased by the National Library on 14 February in Fritze's bookstore in Stockholm.

msItem.title: Revelations
Revelations, Book 1:20-22; 1:45-60
msItem.incipit: multis pro futuro Sicut enim surculus si inseritur trunco arido truncus incipit florere
msItem.explicit: vsquequo veniant ad locum qui mihi placuerit
msItem.note: Several folios are missing in the beginning.

msItem.title: Revelations, Book 2
msItem.rubric: Verba beate brigitte ad christum quare non subtrahat malos antequam veniant ad peccatum. Secundus liber celestium reuelacionum beate brigitte
msItem.explicit: non est licitum tibi scire Sed cum tempus fuerit loquendi

msItem.title: Epistola solitarii ad reges, 1-3
msItem.explicit: ne bonus sponsus castam coniugem et fidelem adultero illudendo exponit

msItem.title: Revelations, Book 8:8-58
msItem.incipit: Ad presentis quippe libri nunc iam materiam descendendo
msItem.explicit: quod ego sum suauis et mitis
msItem.note: The rubric Tercius liber is incorrect.

msItem.title: Revelations, Book 3
msItem.incipit: Ihesus christus deus et homo qui venit in terram assumere humanitatem
msItem.explicit: ut verba Dei per illud diffundantur

msItem.title: Sermo Angelicus
msItem.incipit: CVm beata brigitta principissa regni swecie
msItem.explicit: et regnat deus in secula seculorum Amen

msItem.title: Revelations, Book 5
msItem.incipit: Incipit quintus liber celestium reuelacionum Christi ad beatam Brigittam.
msItem.explicit: Itaque cum veneris ad ista loca ostendam tibi plura etc

msItem.title: Revelations, Book 6:1-109
msItem.incipit: MAter dei loquebatur ad sponsam dicens Ego sum regina celi
msItem.explicit: Ideo dimittatur proprie voluntati, Quia deo accepcius est in mundo iuste viuere et laborare manibus quam in heremo uel religione stare sine dei caritate etc

msItem.title: Revelations, Book 7
msItem.incipit: Iste liber celestium reuelacionum est ultimus
msItem.explicit: inter manus dictarum personarum emisit spiritum.

note.p: The year 1372 in the explicit corrected from 1472.

msItem.title: Excerpts from the Revelations, books 4, 6, 7 and the Revelationes extravagantes
msItem.incipit: Filius dei loquitur quid dixit tibi ille magniloquus et flabeullum ventorum

msItem.note: Several folios are missing in the beginning. The chapter numbers differ somewhat from modern editions of Birgitta's works. Birgitta's Revelations are not presented in order; for example, book 8 is inserted between book 2 and 3.

msItem.title: Excerpts from texts by Simon of Cascia and Bernardinus of Siena
msItem.incipit: Collegerunt pontifices et pharisei concilium et dicebant quod facimus quia hic homo etc
msItem.explicit: qui autem in terra posuerit uel positum non leuauerit morte mulcetur

msItem.title: De emendatione peccatorum
msItem.incipit: NE tardes conuerti ad dominum et ne deferas de die in diem
msItem.explicit: Cui sit honor et gloria et graciarum actio in secula seculorum Amen

msItem.title: Theological text (unidentified)
msItem.incipit: An deum super omnia uel equali dilectione ei aliquod diligas uel creaturam propter eum
msItem.explicit: in quo Christus cenauit cum discipulis

msItem.title: Ars Moriendi QS
msItem.incipit: Quamuis secundum philosophum 3o ethicorum omnium terribilium mors corporis sit terribilissima
msItem.note: This is the version called Ars Moriendi QS after the first words Quamvis secundum. It ends on with a text rubricated Oracio de passione

handDesc.handNote: Hybrida; unlooped b:s, d:s and l:s.

p.note: In pencil in a modern hand (possibly Isak Collijn): notes referring to books and chapters in Birgitta's Revelations.
Upper left margin, in brown ink: manicule.
Bottom of page, in light brown ink, by a contemporary hand: Oracio beate Brigitte with manicule.

decoDesc.p: Capitals touched in red. Chapter numbers and some rubrics in lighter red ink.
